parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty shifter park switch can cause the vehicle to stay on even when turned off, leading to battery drain, and potentially leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's accessories and middle console display stay on when the vehicle is turned off
the vehicle won't shut off completely
the battery drains
and the vehicle may stall or lose power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift control/park switch can cause the vehicle to not shut down properly, leading to battery drain, increased risk of accidents, and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: The engine shuts off but the ignition and auxiliary power remain on
the vehicle won't power down when the start/stop button is pressed
the shift lever is not recognized as being in park
the vehicle may not start or may not turn off when the start/stop button is pressed
the ignition does not turn off when the start/stop button is pressed
intermittent problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission downshifting issue can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle downshifts unexpectedly
the engine revs up to 5
000 RPM
the vehicle accelerates rapidly
the vehicle lurches forward
the vehicle may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked on a slope
the parking brake lever feels stuck or difficult to operate
the brake pads are worn out unevenly
the rear brake calipers are seized or stuck
the parking brake makes strange noises or squeaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake calipers can cause the parking brake to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The rear brake calipers are seized or stuck
the brake pads are worn out unevenly
the parking brake fails to engage
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked on a slope
the brake pads are stuck to the brake discs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake dragging can cause the vehicle to vibrate, overheat, or lose fuel efficiency, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The brakes feel like they are dragging
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the brake pads are worn out unevenly
the rotors are warped
